    Introduction

    This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

    As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

    Base URL

    http://localhost

    Authenticating requests

    To authenticate requests, include an Authorization header with the value "Bearer {token}".

    All authenticated endpoints are marked with a requires authentication badge in the documentation below.

    You can retrieve your token by visiting your dashboard and clicking Generate API token.

    Auth

    Send a reset password link to user email

    requires authentication

    This endpoint allows user to reset their forgotten password.

    Example request:
    curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/auth/forgot-password" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"username\": \"sed\"
}"

    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/auth/forgot-password"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "username": "sed"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://localhost/api/auth/forgot-password',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'username' => 'sed',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
    Received response:
    Request failed with error:

    Request      

    POST api/auth/forgot-password

    Body Parameters

    username  email  

    The email for the password reset link

    Register new user/member

    requires authentication

    This endpoint allows to create new user account.

    Example request:
    curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/auth/register" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"first_name\": \"ut\",
    \"last_name\": \"tempora\",
    \"email\": \"eos\",
    \"gender\": \"animi\",
    \"dob\": \"eum\",
    \"mobile_number\": \"eos\",
    \"password\": \"autem\"
}"

    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/auth/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "first_name": "ut",
    "last_name": "tempora",
    "email": "eos",
    "gender": "animi",
    "dob": "eum",
    "mobile_number": "eos",
    "password": "autem"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://localhost/api/auth/register',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'first_name' => 'ut',
            'last_name' => 'tempora',
            'email' => 'eos',
            'gender' => 'animi',
            'dob' => 'eum',
            'mobile_number' => 'eos',
            'password' => 'autem',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    Request      

    POST api/auth/register

    Body Parameters

    first_name  string  

    User First Name

    last_name  string  

    User Last Name

    email  string  

    user Email

    gender  string  

    User Gender

    dob  string  

    User Date of Birth

    mobile_number  string  

    Mobile Number of User

    password  string  

    User Password

    Get a JWT via given credentials.

    Example request:
    curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/auth/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"username\": \"ea\",
    \"password\": \"reprehenderit\"
}"

    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/auth/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "username": "ea",
    "password": "reprehenderit"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://localhost/api/auth/login',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [

);

    Verify Newly Created User Account

    requires authentication

    This endpoint provides email verification for newly created user accounts

    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/auth/verify/aut" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/auth/verify/aut"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};


fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://localhost/api/auth/verify/aut',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    Example response (401):

    Request      

    GET api/banks/count

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/banks/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=facere" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/banks/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "facere",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};


fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://localhost/api/banks/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'facere',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    Count related models. Alternatively with_count e.g. ?count=relation1,relation2.

    Request      

    GET api/currencies/count

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/currencies/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=quasi" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/currencies/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "quasi",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};


fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://localhost/api/currencies/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'quasi',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search

    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    POST api/auth/reset-password

    requires authentication

    Example request:
    curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/auth/reset-password" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"username\": \"modi\",
    \"token\": \"et\",
    \"password\": \"qui\"
}"

    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/auth/reset-password"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "username": "modi",
    "token": "et",
    "password": "qui"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://localhost/api/auth/reset-password',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'username' => 'modi',
            'token' => 'et',
            'password' => 'qui',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/organisation_member_imports/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=mollitia" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/organisation_member_imports/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "mollitia",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};


fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

$response = $client->get(

            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',

        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:

    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/organisation_accounts/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=perferendis" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"

    Import File

    requires authentication

    Example request:
    curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/organisation_file_imports" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --form "organisation_id=4853752.795" \
    --form "import_to_id=1009660.1168258" \
    --form "import_type=contributions" \
    --form "import_file=@C:\Users\derri\AppData\Local\Temp\php289B.tmp" 
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/organisation_file_imports"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "multipart/form-data",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

const body = new FormData();
body.append('organisation_id', '4853752.795');
body.append('import_to_id', '1009660.1168258');
body.append('import_type', 'contributions');
body.append('import_file', document.querySelector('input[name="import_file"]').files[0]);

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body,
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://localhost/api/organisation_file_imports',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'multipart' => [
            [
                'name' => 'organisation_id',
                'contents' => '4853752.795'
            ],
            [
                'name' => 'import_to_id',
                'contents' => '1009660.1168258'
            ],
            [
                'name' => 'import_type',
                'contents' => 'contributions'
            ],
            [
                'name' => 'import_file',
                'contents' => fopen('C:\Users\derri\AppData\Local\Temp\php289B.tmp', 'r')
            ],
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
    Received response:
    Request failed with error:

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/organisation_group_leaders/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=commodi" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/organisation_group_leaders/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "commodi",
};

    GET api/organisation_groups/count

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/organisation_groups/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=voluptatem" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/organisation_groups/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "voluptatem",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],

            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'voluptatem',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/organisation_invoice_payments/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=incidunt" \

    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/organisation_members/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=quia" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/organisation_members/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "quia",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    GET api/organisation_setting_types/count

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/organisation_setting_types/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=temporibus" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/organisation_setting_types/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "temporibus",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};


fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://localhost/api/organisation_setting_types/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'temporibus',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    GET api/organisation_settings/search

    Query Parameters

    limit  string optional  

    Total items to return e.g. ?limit=15.

    page  integer optional  

    Page of items to return e.g. ?page=1.

    sort  string optional  

    Sorting options e.g. ?sort=field1:asc,field2:asc OR ?sort=latest/oldest.

    count  integer optional  

    Count related models. Alternatively with_count e.g. ?count=relation1,relation2.

    contain  string optional  

    Contain data from related model e.g. ?contain=relation1,relation2.

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/organisation_settings?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/organisation_settings"
);

    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",

};

    Actions: create an invoice for the transaction, return new subscription with invoice

    --data "{
    \"organisation_id\": 87.5588105,
    \"length\": 189778.8674521
}"

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/permissions/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=sit" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/permissions/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "sit",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/sms_accounts/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=voluptatibus" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/sms_accounts/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",

};

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/sms_broadcast_lists/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=repellendus" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/sms_broadcast_lists/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "repellendus",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/subscription_types/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=maiores" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/subscription_types/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "maiores",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    method: "GET",

}).then(response => response.json());

    ]
);

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:

    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/transaction_types/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=asperiores" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/transaction_types/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "asperiores",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};


fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

$response = $client->get(
    'http://localhost/api/transaction_types/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'asperiores',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
